18 "85-2-516. Well logs. (1) Within 60 days after any well is completed, the driller shall file with the
19 bureau a well log report. The bureau shall notify the board of water well contractors established in 2-15-3307 if
20 a submitted well log report was not filed within 60 days of well completion.
21 (2) Except as provided in subsection (3), the well log report must be filed on a form specified by
22 the department in consultation with the board of water well contractors provided for in 2-15-3307 and the
23 bureau. The driller shall provide a location for the well using at least two methods as specified on the form.
24 (3) The bureau may allow submission of the well log report in an electronic format that is in
25 accordance with the form specified as provided in subsection (2).
26 (4) (a) The bureau may return the report to the driller for refiling within 30 days of submission if it is
27 incomplete or incorrect.
